I"j<h1 id="raig-recurrent-aberrations-from-interval-graphs">RAIG: Recurrent Aberrations from Interval Graphs</h1>

<h2 id="about">About</h2>
<p>RAIG is a combinatorial approach to the problem of identifying independent and recurrent copy number aberrations, focusing on the key challenging of separating the overlaps in aberrations across individuals into independent events.</p>

<p><a href="raig.jpg"><img src="raig.jpg" style="width: 600px" /></a></p>

<p><a name="download"></a></p>

<h2 id="downloads">Downloads</h2>
<p>You can download the latest version of RAIG from <a href="http://compbio-research.cs.brown.edu/software/RAIG/RAIG_1.02.tar.gz">RAIG version 1.02</a>.</p>

<p><a name="reference"></a></p>

<h2 id="references">References</h2>
